        "92": {
          "vnum": 92,
          "name": "Temple Library",
          "description": "The temple library consists of little more than two long, low cases of books against the polar walls, facing one another. Perusing the titles as you pass toward the scribe's quarters to the west, you realize they are all in an ancient language, the time of its use long passed. An iron stair at the eastern end of the hall shakes briefly as the library hall hums softly with the energy of the collected knowledge present within the volumes.",
