          "name": "Before the Temple of Esralen",
          "description": "Two solid columns of curved stone rise from the floor here at the end of a wide tunnel travelling north and south. Hinged upon the columns is a sturdy iron gate. Masses of twisting, spindly roots creep out of the earthen ceiling to drape down over the temple entrance, nearly obscuring the carved wooden dragonshead which rests above the gate.",
